To compute $\text{proj}_{\bold{w}} \bold{v}$, we need to find the scalar projection of $\bold{v}$ onto $\bold{w}$. We can do this by first computing the dot product of $\bold{v}$ and $\bold{w}$:

\begin{align*}
\bold{v} \cdot \bold{w} &= (2)(2) + (3)(-1) + (-1)(0) \\
&= 4 - 3 + 0 \\
&= 1
\end{align*}

Next, we need to find the length of $\bold{w}$:

\begin{align*}
|\bold{w}| &= \sqrt{(2)^2 + (-1)^2 + (0)^2} \\
&= \sqrt{5}
\end{align*}

Finally, we can compute the scalar projection of $\bold{v}$ onto $\bold{w}$:

\begin{align*}
\text{proj}_{\bold{w}} \bold{v} &= \frac{\bold{v} \cdot \bold{w}}{|\bold{w}|^2} \bold{w} \\
&= \frac{1}{5} \begin{pmatrix} 2 \\ -1 \\ 0 \end{pmatrix} \\
&= \begin{pmatrix} \frac{2}{5} \\ -\frac{1}{5} \\ 0 \end{pmatrix}
\end{align*}

Therefore, $\text{proj}_{\bold{w}} \bold{v} = \begin{pmatrix} \frac{2}{5} \\ -\frac{1}{5} \\ 0 \end{pmatrix}$.

