\cos \theta & \sin \theta \\
\sin \theta & -\cos \theta
\end{bmatrix}
$$

Using the first identity, we get:

$$
\begin{bmatrix}
x' \\
y'
\end{bmatrix} = 
\begin{bmatrix}
\cos \theta & \sin \theta \\
\sin \theta & -\cos \theta
\end{bmatrix}
