0 \\
-x
\end{bmatrix} = 
\begin{bmatrix}
1 & 0 \\
0 & -1
\end{bmatrix}
\begin{bmatrix}
-3 \\
2
\end{bmatrix}
=
\begin{bmatrix}
1 \\
-2
\end{bmatrix}
$$

Therefore, the point of intersection between the line and the x-axis is $(1,-2)$. We can use this to find the point of intersection between the line and the y-axis:

$$
\begin{bmatrix}
x \\
0
\end{bmatrix} = 
\begin{bmatrix}
1 & 0 \\
0 & -1
\end{bmatrix}
\begin{bmatrix}
-3 \\
2
\end{bmatrix}
